{
  "stem": "4272.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- and we also didn't have anything to cover ourselves with because, right away, when the Germans started the war with Russia, they ordered every Jew to give up every fur they have, even collars from little children's coats, because they needed it to-- to send it to the front or something, for their soldiers.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had a coat at the time that was lined with fur, and I didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I figured, well, they can't see the fur.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And everybody said, but you'll pay with your life for it, if they'll stop you and they'll see it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So in-- in order not to give them the whole thing, I took out the fur and I was left only with the fabric of that coat.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my sister lay down next to me on that bunk that didn't have even straw, not speaking of a cover or a pillow, just bare wood.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She laid down next to me and we covered ourselves, both of us, with that fabric from that coat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's all we had.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What about the food?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the-- the food was-- you know, just-- actually just to survive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just to survive, that's all.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and-- and work, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every-- every morning we were-- we were walked in the middle of the street and forced to go to this ammunition factory.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember that the lights use to flicker in people's windows that lived there, and-- because they were getting ready to go to work.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They got up in their homes and got ready to go to work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I'll never forget, I thought to myself, [CRYING] if I could change to a broom, to a broom, to just be somewhere in a warm corner.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
